"The sixth day of Tishrei marks the Yahrzeit, in 1964, of the Rebbe's mother, Rebbetzin Chana Schneerson. On this day, the Rebbe would customarily deliver a discourse completing the study of a Talmudic Tractate, and would often talk about the vital role of the Jewish woman, gleaning lessons from his mother's life. As the date falls during the high-holiday season, the Rebbe would usually talk on the themes of the holidays and the New Year. This Farbrengen, commemorating the Rebbetzin's 17th Yahrzeit, was televised via satellite around the world"--Container.
